Fortunae rivus, apparently a somewhat inaccurate remi- niscence of the story of Midas, who by bathing in the Pactolus transferred to that river his fatal gift of turning all that he touched to gold. Cp. Ov. Met. xt. r4a—5 rex iussae succedit aquae: vis astrea ‚tinxit flumen et huorono de corpore cessit in omnem. But Prop. 1. 14, 11 tum mihi Pactoli veniunt sub tecto liquores, shows how proverbial the reference had become. For the derivation of mareotim cp. Roby 1. p. aco note.
